AGI - After fears for the truce of recent days, Hamas and Islamic Jihad announced that three hostages will be released tomorrow.&nbsp; Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu confirmed that he had received the names: the Russian-Israeli Alexander Sasha Tropanov, the American-Israeli Sagi Dekel Chen and the 46-year-old of the kibbutz Nir Oz, Yair Horn. It is the sixth round of exchanges of prisoners that arrives after the announcement of Hamas of having frozen the release of the hostages and which made fear for the already fragile truce.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2> Red Cross, very concerned about the conditions of hostages
The International Committee of the Red Cross, which facilitated the exchanges of hostage-prisoners in progress between Israel and Hamas, declared to be "very concerned" for the conditions of prisoners left in Gaza. "The latest release operations strengthen the urgent need for Cicr to access hostage-held people. We are very concerned about the conditions of the hostages," said the Red Cross in a statement on X. "We have constantly reiterated that release and transfer operations must be carried out in a dignified and secure manner. The Cicr will continue our efforts to see all the hostages released until the return of the last prisoner."
&nbsp;
<h2> Sources, Riad will host a summit of Arab countries on Trump's plan
Saudi Arabia will host the leaders of four Arab countries at a summit this month on Donald Trump's proposal for Gaza. A source close to the Saudi government said that representatives of Egypt, Jordan, Qatar and the United Arab Emirates will attend the summit, which will be held before a meeting of the Arab League in Cairo on 27 February.&nbsp;
<h2>Metsola to Ramallah, forward dialogue for lasting peace
"Constructive meeting in Ramallah, with Palestinian representatives and the Secretary-General of the Olp Executive Committee, Hussein al-Sheikh. We will continue to engage in dialogue to achieve lasting peace and stability in the region, offering hope to the Palestinians and security to the Israelis. The first step must be respect for the ceasefire agreement and the release of hostages." He writes on X the President of the European Parliament, Roberta Metsola, visiting the region.
<br> &nbsp;

