&nbsp;
The comprehensive and cutting-edge study program will cover all aspects of cannabis business: from business and business management to cultivation, extraction and marketing. Students will have the opportunity to learn the most innovative techniques and acquire the skills needed to start a successful career in the industry. The initiative has already aroused great interest, with over one hundred enrolment requests for the first thirty places available.
&nbsp;
Cheeba Academy is a concrete response to youth unemployment and an opportunity for economic growth for South Africa, which aims to create 130,000 jobs in cannabis. However, training and licenses to grow cannabis remain costly, raising concerns about access and the possibility that traditional and ancestral growers, depositaries of secular knowledge, are marginalized by new companies. Despite the challenges, the opening of Cheeba Academy marks a historic moment for South Africa >e for the entire African continent, opening the way to new opportunities for economic and professional development in the field of cannabis.&nbsp;
