The one opened by the <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2025-02-12/telefonata-trump-putin-negoziati-fine-guerra-ucraina-29981887/">telefonata</a> of Wednesday between the presidents of the United States and Russia, Donald Trump> and Vladimir Putin>, seems to be a two-game. Zelensky had not been warned of the conversation and did not hide the fear that Kiev could be confronted with the fact accomplished even in the successive stages of the negotiation. Europe, for its part, is likely to have to deploy troops that will have to ensure the security of Ukraine (the head of the Pentagon, Pete Hegseth>, was very clear: the U.S. have no intention of sending peace forces) without having an adequate influence on the diplomatic front.
&nbsp;
Of course, Trump's envoy of the dossier, Keith Kellogg>, should interlocate in the coming days with all NATO allies to collect their views. But the old general is now relegated to a second-floor role, so much so as not to be mentioned by Trump in the message about Truth Social in which he mentioned officials who will conduct a negotiation that, according to the Kremlin, was "immediately". Washington's man on this front is now the envoy for the Middle East, Steve Witkoff>, who, the day before the fateful phone call between the two presidents, flew to Moscow, had spoken for hours with the head of the Kremlin and had returned with Marc Fogel>, the American teacher who was serving in Russia a long detention penalty for possession of drugs (in reality therapeutic cannabis).
&nbsp;
From the president of the European Commission, Ursula von der Leyen>, to the general secretary of NATO, Mark Rutte>, (which seems to play more and more a role as "pompiere" in the comparison between the White House and Brussels), will be over sixty leaders and heads of state and government who will attend the sixty-first edition of the conference, which will be held as usual at the Hotel Bayerischer Hof. Shortly before the call between Trump and Putin, the German government had asserted that it did not expect significant turns on Ukraine. In just one day the situation has evolved rapidly and it is possible that today Vance and Zelensky sign the draft economic agreement presented two days ago in Kiev by the Secretary of the Treasury, Scott Bessent>. Washington aims to access the rare Ukrainian lands and Kiev will have to exploit this claim, since many deposits are located in areas currently occupied by the Russians.
&nbsp;
As for Europeans, it is predictable that the United States will reiterate its demand for increased defence spending from 2% to 5% of GDP. In the absence of an effort in this sense, for the old continent will be much more &nbsp; difficult to have a voice in the chapter in a negotiation that Trump intends to close as soon as possible.

