AGI - The President of the United States, Donald Trump, predicted "wonderful trade agreements" with India during a meeting with Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi at the White House, without giving details. The latter, received in the Oval Studio, assured to hear "the same attachment, the same confidence and the same enthusiasm" that he had during the first term of Donald Trump, which had been marked by a particularly friendly relationship between the two leaders.
&nbsp;
Trump on Modi said: "We have some very important things to talk about. The first is: they will acquire much of our oil and gas. We have more oil and gas than any other country in the world, by far. They need it and we have it," Trump said. Trump added that trade will be a central point of their bilateral talks. He also praised Modi: "He's been a great friend of mine for a long time. We had a wonderful relationship," Trump said.
